               <p>A native of <placeName>Scotland</placeName>, apprenticed in baking, and after
                  moving to <placeName>London</placeName> was employed by <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers1362.xml"/>Thomas Marriott</persName>. He was converted
                  under <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>&apos;s
                  preaching in <date when="1754">1754</date> and became a class leader at the
                  Foundery. In <date when="1757">1757</date> he was accepted as a <seg
                     ana="itinerancy">traveling preacher</seg> (the first one married at that time)
                  and emerged as one of <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"
                  />JW</persName>&apos;s most trusted Assistants. See Atmore, <hi rend="italic"
                     >Memorial</hi>, 256–66; <hi rend="italic">DEB</hi>, 752; <hi rend="italic"
                     >EMP</hi>, 2:158–239; <hi rend="italic">Minutes</hi> (post-Wesley, <date
                     when="1801">1801</date>), 2:82–83; and Vickers, <hi rend="italic"
                     >Dictionary</hi>, 224.</p>
